    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-12T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-12T14:00:00-05:00" n="197"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d197">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">741.6111/3: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-12T22:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 12, 1941—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 12—9:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1346. The British Ambassador informed me this evening that he signed the Pact of
                    Mutual Assistance and its supplementary provision precluding a separate peace
                    with Germany this afternoon at 5 o’clock at the Kremlin.<note n="57"
                        xml:id="d197fn57">Agreement for Joint Action and Mutual Assistance; for
                        text, see League of Nations Treaty Series, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >cciv</hi>, p. 277; or Department of State <hi rend="italic"
                            >Bulletin</hi>, September 27, 1941, p. 240.</note> Stalin was present at
                    the signature.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
